.TH man 3 "15 March 2021" "1.0" "_printf man page"
.SH NAME
_printf \- prints formatted string 
.SH SYNOPSIS
int printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf() is a series of functions that can be used to print a formatted string
by using a serious of characters, format specifiers and flags.

.SS Format of the format string
Format points to a character string that can contain zero or more regular
characters or format specifiers starting with a '%' character and followed
by a subsequent argument to be passed after format
.SS Conversion specifiers
Each '%' will be followed by a character to indicate the type of specifier
Here are all the specifiers handles by this function:

c		used to specify a single character

s		specifies a string of characters

d, i		integers are specified using these characters

b		converts an unsigned integer to its binary equivalent

%		prints a modulus

.SH SEE ALSO
printf(3), puts(3), scanf(3)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Zidane Gimiga
